<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/93379298-david"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1622330956i/93379298._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/93379298-david">David</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It&apos;s definitely not definitive as an all-encompassing book. As Bob stated, it&apos;s very much focused on military engagements and very little politics. Fo<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It's definitely not definitive as an all-encompassing book. As Bob stated, it's very much focused on military engagements and very little politics. Foote is a Lost Cause supporter and does not write much about slavery other than to quote Lincoln in stating that his goal is unification, not emancipation.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

