  <span id="freeText4603201114601862556" style="display:none">There are books that you read that sometimes just pull you in, even if you know how it is going to end. This is one of those books. Shelby Foote took a period in our nation and laid it open as a true storyteller. I enjoyed the book immensely. The stories told in these pages have sparked my interest in research of the subject and more importantly; other books to read. This book is a novel, but in the pages you will find some of the best storytelling that is factually sound. Thank you Shelby Foote for bring to life the names of people from our past. My only wish is that I would have had the opportunity to thank you in person for such a wonderful book. I consider it a true work of art. </span>
